<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[150,1436,151,468]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Plantae erectae, ramosae, usque ad 
<quantity box="[547,612,189,212]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="cm" value="50.0">50 cm</quantity>
altae. Caulis basi ad 
<quantity box="[856,941,189,212]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
diametro, setis flavescentis, glandulis et pilis scabridis brevissimis obtectus. Folia alterna, lamina ovata vel rhomdoidea, basi cuneata, apice acuminata, margine irregulariter lobata, lobis 1–2(–3) in uno latere, ovatis margine serratis. Calyx tubo turbinato, lobis ovatiacuminatis, 
<quantity box="[329,387,285,308]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
longis et 
<quantity box="[492,549,285,308]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
latis; corolla expansa; petala alba, oblonga, cymbiformia, 
<quantity box="[1185,1270,285,308]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7 mm</quantity>
longa, 
<quantity box="[1350,1435,285,308]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 mm</quantity>
lata, dente triangulari in utrisque lateribus 
<quantity box="[668,754,317,340]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
a basi remoto provisa, dorso esetosa, glandulosa et dense pilis scabridis instructa.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
